Install Home Assistant Core
(Source: https://www.home-assistant.io/installation/raspberrypi)

Checking for Pi Updates:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get update -y

Install dependencies:
sudo apt-get install -y python3 python3-dev python3-venv python3-pip libffi-dev libssl-dev libjpeg-dev zlib1g-dev autoconf build-essential libopenjp2-7 libtiff5 libturbojpeg0-dev tzdata

Creating an Account:
sudo useradd -rm homeassistant -G dialout,gpio,i2c

Creating the virtual environment:
sudo mkdir /srv/homeassistant
sudo chown homeassistant:homeassistant /srv/homeassistant

Change to the virtual environment:
sudo -u homeassistant -H -s
cd /srv/homeassistant
python3 -m venv .
source bin/activate

Installing required Python package:
python3 -m pip install wheel

Installing Home Assistant Core:
pip3 install homeassistant
hass (When you run the hass command for the first time, it will download, install and cache the necessary libraries/dependencies. This procedure may take anywhere between 5 to 10 minutes. During that time, you may get “site cannot be reached” error when accessing the web interface.

GUI URL:
http://homeassistant.local:8123 or http://localhost:8123 or http://X.X.X.X:8123
